# CDP (Chrome DevTools Protocol)

## Starting Cursor with CDP

```powershell
# Start Cursor IDE with remote debugging enabled
cursor --remote-debugging-port=9222
```

This exposes CDP on `localhost:9222`. The server discovers available targets via `http://localhost:9222/json`.

## CDP Client (cdp-client.js)

Lightweight WebSocket-based CDP client. Key methods:

- `evaluateJSON(expression)` - Evaluate JS in Cursor's main frame, auto-detects async and sets `awaitPromise` accordingly
- `evaluate(expression)` - Raw evaluate, returns CDP result object
- `send(method, params)` - Send any CDP command

## DOM Extraction (dom-extractor.js)

A large JavaScript string that gets evaluated inside Cursor IDE via CDP. It extracts:

- Chat messages (user and assistant)
- Message parts: text, code blocks (with diffs), tool calls, todo lists
- Agent status (running, stopped, tool name)
- Current mode and model
- Input editor content and placeholder text

The extraction script finds elements by CSS selectors matching Cursor's internal DOM structure. Key selectors:

- `.composer-content` - Main chat message container
- `.agentic-composer-tool-call-group` - Tool call groups
- `.slim-code-render`, `.slim-diff-render` - Code blocks and diffs
- `.composer-unified-dropdown` - Mode selector
- `.composer-unified-dropdown-model` - Model selector

## Machine Manager (machine-manager.js)

Manages connections to one or more machines running Cursor with CDP:

- Discovers CDP targets at configurable intervals
- Connects to page-type targets
- Runs `dom-extractor.js` on each target at polling intervals
- Broadcasts extracted state to web clients via Socket.IO
- Handles target disconnect/reconnect gracefully

## Command Execution

The server can send commands back to Cursor IDE:

- `send_message` - Types text into Cursor's input and submits
- `stop_generation` - Clicks the stop button
- `set_mode` - Opens mode dropdown and clicks the target mode
- `set_model` - Opens model dropdown and clicks the target model
- `get_mode_options` / `get_model_options` - Extracts available options from dropdowns

All commands use JavaScript `.click()` injection (not mouse events) for reliability.
